Imagine you have a big box of toys, and you want to send it to your friend. But, the box is too big to send all at once. So, you decide to break it down into smaller boxes, let's call them "chunks".

When we send data (like a file or a message) over the internet, we break it down into smaller chunks.

Each chunk is sent separately, and then the receiver puts all the chunks together to get the original data.

